data.title: CONTENTdm
data.meta_description:
Eternal Sounds was a band originating from Hillsboro, Oregon that played together from 1966-1967. Original members of the Eternal Sounds included Bob Claycamp, Mike Austin, Steven Crockett, Charlie Cook, and Ron Reedy. They began playing at after game dances and special events and entered a battle of the bands competition at the Hillsboro Armory where they met their soon to be manager Bud Garrison. Garrison worked for Sunn Musical Equipment and entered them into a contract and began booking them through an agency. A couple of years later they changed their name to "The Music Box".

Jini Dellaccio 74
